    "created_at": "2016-11-25T22:13:56Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-11-25T22:13:56Z",
    "body": "Hi, I've had a similar issue in browser Chrome/Opera, here is what I did which seems to fix the issue.\r\n```\r\nvar refreshCanvas = function() {\r\n    var canvasEls = document.getElementsByTagName('canvas');\r\n    for(var i = 0; i < canvasEls.length; i++){\r\n        canvasEls[i].width -= 1;\r\n    }\r\n    setTimeout(function(){\r\n        for(var i = 0; i < canvasEls.length; i++){\r\n            canvasEls[i].width += 1;\r\n        }\r\n    },0);\r\n};\r\ndocument.removeEventListener(\"visibilitychange\",refreshCanvas, false);\r\ndocument.addEventListener(\"visibilitychange\",refreshCanvas, false);\r\n```\r\n\r\nHope this can help :)"
